On Thursday, Ms Pelosi warned in a written statement that "if the United Kingdom chooses to undermine the Good Friday accords, the Congress cannot and will not support a bilateral free trade agreement with the United Kingdom". However, responding to this, DUP leader Sir Jeffrey Donaldson said that it is the Northern Ireland protocol which is undermining the Good Friday agreement. He said: "If Nancy Pelosi wants to see the agreement protected then she needs to recognise that it is the protocol that is harming and undermining the agreement and that is why we need to deal with it." FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES... 